<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1431,2018]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1591,1617]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antenna 
<number box="[443,458,1592,1618]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="2.0">2</number>
subequal in length to the body. Upper lip rounded, more produced than epistome. Mandible, palp 
<number box="[340,352,1632,1658]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
-articulate, article 
<number box="[572,587,1632,1658]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="2.0">2</number>
slender and elongate, length 
<date box="[939,975,1632,1658]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<number box="[939,953,1632,1658]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="6.0">6</number>
X
</date>
the width, with 
<number box="[1174,1189,1632,1658]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="6.0">6</number>
distal setae, without setae in the ventral and dorsal margins, article 
<number box="[703,719,1672,1698]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
, slightly falcate, length 
<date box="[1004,1039,1672,1698]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<number box="[1004,1018,1672,1698]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="4.0">4</number>
X
</date>
the width, minutely setose, without setae on the dorsal margin, with two ventral setae and three apical setae. Gnathopod 
<number box="[1185,1200,1712,1738]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
, basis slightly elongate, length 
<number box="[295,332,1752,1778]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="2.2">2.2</number>
X the width. Pereopod 
<number box="[604,620,1752,1778]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
, merus, carpus and propodus, posterior margin with plumose setae in both sexes. Pereopod 
<number box="[406,420,1792,1818]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="6.0">6</number>
with posterior margin concave. Telson with distal margin truncate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
